CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F315A1778533866
OL,3,CJohn Swinney rules out talks with
OL,4,CReform as new MSPs arrive at Holyrood
OL,6,FLittle is expected to change after the
OL,7,FSNP continued its domination of
OL,8,FHolyrood, winning 58 seats, with
OL,9,FLabour and Reform UK with 17 seats and
OL,10,Fthe Greens on 15.
OL,12,FThe Scottish Greens have regularly
OL,13,Fbacked the SNP-led government's plans
OL,14,Fin recent years and their record
OL,15,Fnumber of MSPs return yet another pro-
OL,16,Findependence majority.
OL,18,FThe Scottish Conservatives slumped to
OL,19,F12 seats and the Lib Dems increased
OL,20,Ftheir share to 10.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G2/9
